      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COBALT WINTER (4) jumped cleanly from the rails last start to lead all the way and score (20.06) at this track in a TG1-4W over 342m. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can measure up again. ELEGANT FLINT (1) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish 1.5 lengths away in third (23.25) at Gawler in a Grade 6 over 400m. Hard to beat again. ROYALE MAPLE (2) resumed from a break finishing fifth (17.24) at Murray Bridge Straight in a Grade 6. Will strip fitter for the run. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from three starts. Should be about the mark. NUDGE UNIT (7) is fresh from a short break and ready to run well.",
